The paper discusses security issues related to memory encryption schemes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves building a software-based memory encryption solution, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses hardware extensions provided by Intel and AMD, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves demonstrating a proof-of-concept attack, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
